Could you please find the 'external/protobuf/cmake/protoc' and run 
```
ldd external/protobuf/cmake/protoc
```
, and give me the output.

the output is:
        linux-vdso.so.1 =>  (0x00007fff763a2000)                                           
        libstdc++.so.6 => /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libstdc++.so.6 (0x00007f76a15d9000)      
        libgcc_s.so.1 => /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libgcc_s.so.1 (0x00007f76a13c3000)              
        libc.so.6 => /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6 (0x00007f76a0ff9000)

        libm.so.6 => /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libm.so.6 (0x00007f76a0cf0000)

It's a compiler bug. libpthread should be there but it isn't.
What's your compiler version? Are you using the system compiler or gcc from anaconda?

just system compiler /usr/bin/gcc
gcc version is 5.4.0

Hi snnn,
you said,
Need to insert '--no-as-needed' before the '-pthread' arg in the link command args of protoc.
how can I do in onnxruntime.
It need be done in protobuf.
so I have to rebuild my profobut?

Google need to fix the problem in protobuf first, then we'll pick up the fix. But Google may not do it because this is more like a compiler bug.  If you upgrade your operating system and compiler to a newer version, the problem will be gone.  

I'll close this bug because there isn't anything we can do.

issue.title: Fix lto bug for protobuf and ubuntu

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

see #2060

Before my change, protoc was built as:
/usr/lib/ccache/c++   -flto -O3 -DNDEBUG -march=native -mtune=native -flto -fno-fat-lto-objects  -rdynamic CMakeFiles/protoc.dir/__/src/google/protobuf/compiler/main.cc.o  -o protoc libprotobuf.a libprotoc.a libprotobuf.a -lpthread /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libz.so

But if you run ldd, you'll find pthread is missing.

$ ldd ./external/protobuf/cmake/protoc
        linux-vdso.so.1 (0x00007ffc7bec0000)
        libc.so.6 => /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6 (0x00007f5c78d0e000)
        libstdc++.so.6 => /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libstdc++.so.6 (0x00007f5c78b2c000)
        libgcc_s.so.1 => /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libgcc_s.so.1 (0x00007f5c78b12000)
        /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 (0x00007f5c7925b000)
        libm.so.6 => /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libm.so.6 (0x00007f5c789c4000)



**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.
